Why bother with an unaccredited program and one that by its own admission will never get such a thing?It's not like there's any lack of comparable schools that are accredited.I don't know how many employers check for that sort of thing, but if even 10 per cent do, it could include the outfit you really want to work for.Degrees follow you around for a long time. I changed jobs twice in my 50s and the first thing I had to deal with in terms of the HR gauntlet was my degree transcripts. My hiring manager didn't care half as much as HR, but in big companies, HR can veto if they don't like the answers they get.There's a lot of "checkmark-ism" especially at big companies.Quote:I know who got their PE's are civil engineers working on buildings/roadsMy brother is a mechanical engineer, and he got his PE. He worked (still works) in the steel industry.
