Does anyone know what accreditation does for grad school admissions?A PE is a nice discussion, but I got my Masters in my '40s, long after I assumed I was done with college.I would certainly hate to learn after the fact that not being accredited for my undergrad blackballed me from any (never mind many) grad schools.The other problem is, today's answer may not be enough. Sometimes, these things ratchet up over time.Back when my wife was getting into Nursing, not having a bachelor's was no impediment to a fine career. But, fast forward a couple of decades and now it is. She no longer qualifies for jobs that her experience certainly qualifies her for.
