I did a little looking into info about the PE and basically since the licensing is regulated at the state level if you work on products that could be sold across state lines a PE license is not required. So it makes sense that the only people that seem to need them are those working civil engineering projects and construction sites/buildings.Still, as was pointed out earlier a lot of employers will have words in job requisitions that require a degree from an ABET accredited program. One problem with some of these types of curricula are that there's no lab time. That's not great for an engineering degree. Probably a major reason why it would not be accredited.
